        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-04T07:25:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "WARNING: That\u0027s not how this is supposed to work. If the client buffer is small but spans two guest pages, the message will be spent as two separate pipe buffers!! The implementation may even split them into two separate sendBuffers() calls, depending on the kernel driver code.\n\nYou cannot make such assumptions. And there is no framing in the pipe protocol, so you should either use fixed-size messages (which may involved multiple AndroidPipeBuffers), or use some sort of custom framing (e.g. hex4 payload len + payload).",
      "revId": "a4dd471e0da2bdc69eda1940eb9d32b4757d10c4",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
